            <biogHist>
                <p>Margaret or Peggy MacNeil was born c1810, most probably in Barra where she
                    appears to have remained throughout her life; there is no record of the names of
                    her parents. By the time of the 1851 census Margaret is listed as being married
                    to John MacNeil, a cottar and fisherman, both recorded as being aged 40 and
                    living in Bruairnis with their five children: Michael (13), Elizabeth (9),
                    Donald (7), Dougald (5), and Mary (1). In 1861 census they are listed as
                    occupying one of the farms at Bayheriva [Bàgh Thiarabhagh] and John is working
                    as a fisherman; their daughter Mary is not recorded in this census. In the 1871
                    Census Peggy is living alone with her daughter, named Catherine, in Bruairnis
                    where they are classed as paupers. Margaret's death is not recorded.</p>
                <p>Alexander Carmichael visited Margaret on 30 September 1870 and collected the song
                    'Cha Teid Mor A Bharraidh Bhronach' from her.</p>
